radiographic_examinations.findings: Spine and hip t scores were –2.02 and –1.74, both indicating osteopenia and an increased risk of fracture.
radiographic_examinations.changes_over_time: A dual X-ray absorptiometry scan at 1 year showed that her spine and hip t scores had improved by 7% and 9% to –1.87 and –1.58, respectively.
